caption: I went here every morning if a vacation to the area and i loved it! The man working at the counter was so friendly and accommodating. The breakfast sandwiches are amazing and well-priced. I love the Korean fusion! Coffee is good and there's a fun selection of baked goods too! Highly recommend!

So good! Egg everything with the salmon , cream cheese, and scallion was superb. The salmon was not stringy, the bagel was perfect, and there’s some spicy sauce on there that’s pretty on point. The coffee is above average for the area for sure with that little bit of extra nuttiness or toasty goodness that puts it above deli stuff or blech Starbucks.

(Translated by Google) It's a small shop, but the coffee is delicious. I ordered a latte, but the fragrance was good and the price was reasonable. The food seemed to be delicious with the main menu of light meals. There was no one when I came to the store, but the seats are separated by large transparent vinyl, so I can rest assured if there is a person next to me. There were only two tables in the seats. The clerk was also friendly and pleasant. A shop where you can relax and spend time comfortably.  (Original) 小さなお店だが、コーヒーは美味しい。ラテを頼んだが香りもよかったし値段も妥当だった。食事も軽食メインのメニューで美味しそうだった。来店したときは誰もいなかったが、席が大きな透明なビニールで仕切られているので、もし隣に人がいたとしても安心できる。座席は2つのテーブルしかなかった。店員もフレンドリーで感じがよかった。ふらりと入って気持ちよく過ごせるお店。
Great food and drinks for reasonable prices! They are always so friendly :)
My go to cafe in the neighborhood. I always get the avocado mash with bacon. Absolutely delish!
Everything is perfect!  The shrimp avocado on toast never disappoints.
One of my favorite cafes in this neighborhood. Good quality coffee and wonderful food.
Great service, delicious espresso!
Squirrel drawings, great coffee, bagel with ramen👌
The line was out the door when we arrived but we were able to order and be seated in 15 minutes. Food was good and staff was friendly and helpful
Small hole in the wall coffee shop. Super nice owner. Dog friendly and has outdoor seating if needed. I used to study and do work here.

I was introduced to 19 Café by a beautiful young woman with the testimony of a great iced coffee about two months ago. But on that day I decided to also try their kimchi rice with chicken. That is some of the best rice I have ever had and have eaten that meal 1 to 3 times a week since the first visit. The coffee is excellent as well but to think that I would find such a great meal from a little cafe was such a surprise. I highly recommend everyone give this place a try.
Amazing best coffee ever. Love it.
Love this spot. Excellent coffee and customer service!
Amazing place always nice and clean. A+

My friend and I happened to wander into this gem after having lunch. I got a matcha latte which was well prepared. We were impressed with their food menu and saw lots of customers having ramen. My friend and I will defiantly be back to try their food. The atmosphere was really nice and the staff was friendly. I highly reccommend!
Quaint little coffee shop. Nice people, cool vibe, good food!!
We had some delicious muffin and coffee.
Super sweet owners, and they get the job done as a Cafe. When I was going in it seemed like they knew everyone that walked in so it had a very comfortable atmosphere.

You need to get breakfast at 19 Cafe! What a great, cozy little place. The breakfast bagel sandwiches are fantastic, filling, and priced very reasonably. Coffee was tasty. The folks working are friendly and prompt. I wish we had found this place earlier!

I love going here. I usually get a bagel egg sandwich. my favorite so far being the kale, egg, cheddar (trying the open face sandwiches today). I get a matcha latte with oat milk with an extra chai, wait for my beautifully made breakfast, and have slowly been making my way through "The Illustrated Man", a collection of short stories by Ray Bradbury. It's a five minute walk from my apartment and I could not be happier. I want people to know how awesome they are, but I also don't want crowds, but they are so great I had to review. I will say, it's a small operation (much like this beautiful goulash spot I used to go to in Berlin), and two people essentially run the entire thing. If you are in a rush, maybe not the best spot, but that's good - there are places for that and the ambiance of this place makes you want to linger.
This is a great coffee in NYC! Can't wait to come back :)

(Translated by Google) Super fine coffee (cappuccino can be compared with Italy) and large selection of different breakfast variations (toast, bagles). These are all delicious. Friendly restrained service. We were there every morning.  (Original) Super feiner Kaffee (Cappuccino lässt sich mit Italien messen) und grosse Auswahl an verschiedenen Frühstück Variationen (Toast, Bagles). Diese sind alle sehr lecker. Freundliche zurückhaltende Bedienung. Wir waren jeden Morgen dort.
beautiful environment, beautiful plating, beautiful tastes, beautiful coffee, beautiful barista ;)
I don’t think this place is open.
Jason is the greatest, and his 19 Café is a neighborhood asset ☕️🎷🎶🥘
Good cakes

Very cute and small spot. I had the pork soup with soba. It was good, however I was still hungry after I was done. I didn't try anything else, but other people were eating next to me and they're sandwiches looked delicious. Please be aware that the menu prices on Google are incorrect, also that they no longer serve pork belly 😑 because people were complaining about the calories. They now serve roast pork. Overall, I likes it and will come back for a sandwich instead of the soup.
Nice hip little place. Good food at good prices.

Great coffee and cafe food with a sort of Korean-American flair (ramen, kimchi as an add on, bulgogi sandwiches alongside avo on toast, bagels etc). Seating is plentiful, service is very friendly, and there are cute squirrel drawings on the walls that I’ve become super fond of. 5 stars.

Loved this place! It was my last day in Brooklyn and wish I had seen this place the first day! Great ice coffee and bagels! Delicious! And very inviting atmosphere! Very welcoming vibe from the owner too! When I return to New York I will return!!
There is always tast difference in 19 and king its rather a chance of 10/2 but its always tasty
Great Spot! Get the Avocado Mash, it’s Amazing. Really nice staff too. Love this place.
This cafe has the best bacon egg and cheese i have ever eaten and the ramen was amazing.

The coffee tasted just fine and the mood was not bad, but it was not exactly pretty. I do not think you need to come here unless you're looking for cafes everywhere. I give them a big A+, everything was good!
Exquisite Cafe!  Almond Chocolate Cookies in a Feast to Happiness! Friendly Staff Endeauvor upon Scenary In Nature Diversified.
Best bacon and egg sandwich ever
What a wonderful cozy place to have something and relax with a cup of good coffee. Carefully-made foods, great service. Every neighborhood deserves this kind of coffee place, I daringly argue.

Asked for a double shot latte,got charged for a quad shot. That was ok because needed the caffine, but what I got was a extremly hot, weak and improperly steamed coffee. Only plus was service was nice

Really nice place to come with your laptop and work. Lattes are good, and I've even had the ramen a couple times. It's really not bad for ramen from a cafe. And both times the ramen came with BBQ pork inside, which tasted really great.

Friendly barista! Consistently good coffee.  dim lighting. I had a three shot cortado with little to no foam and a nice smokey aftertaste. I will continue supporting this small cafe because I only go where theres' good coffee.
Amazing little spot. Cozy feel. Really nice owner. Great coffee and cool food - breakfast, ramen - basically exactly my kind of place. A gem in this neighborhood.
Nice
Very cute place! Nice vibe, friendly service, good breakfast sandwiches!
This is really a nice place. The food & coffee is really tastey. And the staff is very nice. I'm a Starbucks lover, but I like this place better... it's more personal... Great job guys!!!
Great food and coffee at a reasonable price. There’s a good amount of seating too.
Great spot and great food !
lovely atmosphere in the coziest part of Bushwick
Small, adequate, breakfast and lunch options, decent prices.
Great coffee great bagels

Hidden gem. And recently renovated too, making better use of the surprisingly big space. Coffee like anywhere else, but also wonderful Asian-inspired bagels, sandwiches, and bowls. Even the egg, avocado, cream cheese bagel comes with the slightest hint of a tangy/sweet/spicy mystery sauce that adds another dimension to what would otherwise be any other breakfast experience. Soft music selection; perfect for work or study.

(Translated by Google) It is a small cafe, quiet, it looks clean, we only entered for a coffee, I did not like the service very much.  (Original) Es un café pequeño, tranquilo, se ve limpio , sólo entramos por un café,  no me gustó mucho el servicio.
Great customer service and food. The atmosphere was calming for a quick mid-day cup of coffee

Best kept secret in this part of Willy-B. It's a great place to relax at any time of the day, enjoy the chill atmosphere, answer some emails or read a book. Try the Avocado Toast, it's amazing. The coffee is also phenomenal. I LOVE THIS PLACE!

The place is quite narrow and dark, but it has a nice calming atmosphere. The wait is a bit longer than expected, but the food looked and tasted delicious when it arrived. One thing they could improve on is the menu..it's on a chalkboard and handwrittened..so a bit difficult to read for those with poor vision. It doesn't seem like they have a paper menu for easy viewing.

Im staying at an airbnb very close to this café, and it has been a life saver, great service, coffee, food (my god they do some mean bagels!) fairly priced, and they even have really cool music (iron and wine, the beatles, Papa M, etc). A blessing!
Hands down favorite place in the area.  Friendly owner with a great vibe.
Love this place. Lovely owners and super cozy
Awesome bagels, great coffee. You won't get a better deal for 10$!
It’s very cozy in here
Great coffee, food, and atmosphere. Try the Paris sandwich!
The avocado toast is very good (comes with spicy mayo and an egg).
Very friendly and helpful service. Ordered two coffees and two bagel sandwiches. The coffee was strong and the bagels were delicious. Also had classic rock playing with some cute decor.

Never again.  After waiting 30 minutes for a Kale and Egg snawhich, I️ simply left. The “kitchen” was a mess, with uncooked bacon and half done jobs lying all around. Don’t waste your money.
This place is wonderful! The coffee is great, it's super cozy and quiet to come in and work on your laptop, and the people are so friendly! My new favorite place.

Thanks for the awesome coffee and the sandwiches!

Great coffee, staff and ramen. Awesome quiet, chill atmosphere.

I love this little cafe. The gentleman that runs this place is so lovely, the coffee is great, and the food is simple and delicious. I just had the kale, cheddar, egg toast with bacon and I'm surprised to be this impressed by a breakfast sandwich. Great spot to sit and read/write or meet with a friend.
Loved the atmosphere! Beautiful drawing by the owner's wife, great coffee, even the decaf. Needs better ventilation due to frying, also vegan food would be great.

Like everybody says: warm, friendly people, wonderful coffee, great food, clean environment.
Very warm, kind staff and wonderful coffee and pastries. Environment feels very safe and tucked away. I always come here for coffee on my lunch break!
I had the marinated grilled chicken sandwich and it was one of the best sandwiches ive ever had. Super nice staff/very cozy, will be coming back!
Super cosy cafe and very nice people. A rare bird when you live in montrose avenue ! The Californie fried Rice is amazing. GO there !
Excellent coffee and delicious scones. Very friendly and relaxed place.
The space is lovely and the food/drinks are thoughtfully made. The owner seems to live here and just about does it all. I'd recommend the ramen & specialty lattes.
Great food and reasonably priced. You might have to wait for the service and the space sort of pieced together but everything is freshly made and it makes a great local spot.
